ASABA – Ahead of the 2023 General Elections, the Head of Umuokonogwu quarters, Ibusa, near Asaba, Delta State, Onowu Mathias Onukuwutelu Asiodu has urged Nigerians, irrespective of their social status, to vote wisely for the emergence of credible, resourceful and God fearing candidates in any of their chosen political parties that would refloat the economy and revamp the badly battered image of the country in the comity of nations. High chief Asiodu who spoke to Journalists yesterday while celebrating his 90th birthday, lamented the inability of the political class to translate the human and mineral resources, into development. Peeved about the tatty State of the nation today, the nonagenarian who is living in perpetual peace, and comfort, tasked all and Sundry to take their destiny in their own hands to ensure that they vote for the candidate and not the party for a better Nigeria. He said, “Well, I cannot tell anyone to vote party A or B, but I know everyone has a conscience, if so, then vote your conscience for a candidate, and not the party, for the betterment of the country. “I know too that every candidate has rolled out his manifestos for the sake of the Election, but it is now left for us to peruse them carefully and vote accordingly to bring us out of the mess we are going through today,” the prime minister advised. He also advised the Youth to shun the get rich quick syndrome, cultism and other social vices, saying that they lead one to untimely death. While lamenting the killings of youth via Cultism in Nigeria, he cautioned them to focus more on what will better their lives, and the image of the country, noting that kidnapping is evil which must be avoided by engaging in productive ventures such as trade and education, as his children who are doing well in their chosen careers.